      <akn:section eId="sec_3_1442">
        <akn:num>3-1442</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Commission organization; members; meetings.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1442_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1442_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1442_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor shall appoint the chairperson of the Commission from among the public members. All members shall serve without compensation, but shall be eligible for reimbursement of expenses as provided in ยง 1-611.08(d).</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1442_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Commission shall develop its own rules of procedure.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1442_e">
      <akn:num>(e)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Commission shall meet at least once every other month. The meetings shall be held in the District and shall be open to the public. A quorum to transact business shall consist of a majority plus one of the public members.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
